node.text:
[Warning: graphic video content] Today is one of the best days of my entire life. 🏳️‍⚧️ Words somewhat fail me because all I can keep repeating over and over again is “oh my gosh I’m so happy” and “I can’t believe this is real.” What a powerful day and moments I’ll never forget for the rest of my life. I feel like my life is truly just beginning and I can’t thank each and every one of you enough. If you’re reading this then you are part of my story and have helped make this happen for me. 🤟

Kelsey, my love, happy two year anniversary baby! I can’t believe how lucky I am to be loved by you and to create this life together. To have a partner as loving and supportive as you is a dream come true. You are the definition of what those words mean. I love you to the moon!

There will be many more “chest reveals” to come as I continue to heal. 🤗 Get ready for all of the shameless shirtless selfies… 😍 I’m absolutely in love with and obsessed with my new chest.

Love,
Luke

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Luke Wesley Pearson on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and indoor.

node.text:
Woke up from a nap today feeling grateful as ever for the access to gender affirming care that I have. 🏳️‍⚧️🙏

@getplume breaks down those barriers. When I was ready to start T, I was SO READY. So eager, excited, and anxious to start right away. I signed up for Plume after learning about their app-based care and it was like the skies cleared for me. I had a virtual call with one of their healthcare providers (50%+ of them are LGBTQ+!), and within 24 hours my first Rx was ready for pick up.

For so many in the community there are hoops and hurdles that healthcare providers will try to make us go through in order to get a Rx. We have to be our number one advocate and choose carefully who we tell our story and medical history to. It can be scary not knowing who you can trust in the healthcare space as a transgender person. Just because someone is a doctor definitely doesn’t mean they are educated on transgender people and transgender healthcare, nor does it mean they aren’t transphobic 🥴. Trust me… my dad is a doctor and based on things he has said my eyes have been opened to just how horrifically uneducated and transphobic doctors can be. We do not communicate anymore, and that is part of the healthy boundaries I am setting for mine, Kelsey’s, and our future children’s lives. He doesn’t get a part in my story anymore.

🏳️‍⚧️ There are two types of testosterone: Testosterone Cypionate and Testosterine Enanthate. The only difference is the oil the T is in! For the first 4 months I was using T-Cypionate and after each subQ shot in my belly I would get an extremely itchy hive-like lump that would harden and last for 6-7 days or longer. I read that that can be somewhat common so dealt with it for awhile. Then I asked my provider @getplume and they told me about T-Enanthate and that some people have allergic reactions to the other one, and called me in a new Rx. I’ve since done two shots of T-Enanthate and have had zero hard itchy lumps! 🥳👏🏳️‍⚧️

I share this in hopes that if you’re experiencing what I did you know to ask about other options! There are many different types of ways to take testosterone too outside of injections. This is just what I prefer. :)

node.text: Living, working, and being with your partner 24/7/365 takes a lot of love first and foremost, as well as patience, communication, and respect. Kels is my best friend, my soulmate, and the love of my life. The way she has loved me and supported me throughout our entire relationship but especially through my transition is something I can’t thank her and love her enough for. 🙏🏳️‍⚧️ I think all any of us want in this world is to be loved unconditionally, and Kels has truly shown me what that means and feels like. I cannot wait to watch her be a mom and to grow our family and our life together. I feel safe and secure with her. Our love isn’t always exciting, adventurous, and loud - it’s calm, steady, and consistent. @kelseystacypearson is my home, and I am so damn proud to be her husband. 🔒♥️

node.text:
The relief I feel to be home after the last two weeks is making a world of difference in my mental health. I’ve had so much anxiety like I am going to “mess something up” or do something wrong. I felt fragile and vulnerable for days. Having a major surgery in another city and state, recovering in Airbnb’s and hotels, and having no sense of normalcy or consistency really adds a layer to the complex emotions I’ve had. As soon as we got home yesterday I immediately felt a wave of relief, safety, comfort, and I feel like I can fully appreciate and love the way everything turned out. 🙏🏡❤️

Thank you to everyone who has shown me so much love and support. I mentally and physically don’t have the capacity to respond to every message or comment, but please know that I see you and am so grateful for you! 🥰🏳️‍⚧️

node.text:
About my wife ❤️‍🔥

She is the most selfless, warm, and loving wife, partner, and best friend. We are literally together 24/7/365 yet no amount of time is ever enough! She makes me feel like I’m the only person in the world She makes me feel handsome. 🙏 She is my sun, my moon, and my stars. She has encouraged me—and empowered me—to become the man I have always wanted to be, and I don’t think she even realizes how much better she has made my life since day 1. She is everything to me.

This love is so rare and I will cherish every moment I get to be with you @kelseystacypearson. Happy 2 year anniversary baby! ❤️‍🔥

Swipe for some of my favorite photos from the past 2 weeks ❤️ I love my little family and can’t wait for it to grow in the future.

node.text:
[Warning: graphic video content] Today is one of the best days of my entire life. 🏳️‍⚧️ Words somewhat fail me because all I can keep repeating over and over again is “oh my gosh I’m so happy” and “I can’t believe this is real.” What a powerful day and moments I’ll never forget for the rest of my life. I feel like my life is truly just beginning and I can’t thank each and every one of you enough. If you’re reading this then you are part of my story and have helped make this happen for me. 🤟

Kelsey, my love, happy two year anniversary baby! I can’t believe how lucky I am to be loved by you and to create this life together. To have a partner as loving and supportive as you is a dream come true. You are the definition of what those words mean. I love you to the moon!

There will be many more “chest reveals” to come as I continue to heal. 🤗 Get ready for all of the shameless shirtless selfies… 😍 I’m absolutely in love with and obsessed with my new chest.

Love,
Luke
